malicious_clones.name: Claude Chat Notifier

malicious_clones.name: Claudette
malicious_clones.evidence: The suspect extension 'Claudette' is a malicious clone of 'Claude'. It deliberately uses the distinctive terracotta brand color of the anchor to create visual association. The name is a direct feminine diminutive of the anchor's name. By combining the anchor's visual identity (the specific background color) with the brand name in the title and description, the developer is attempting to siphon users from the official 200k+ user extension to their 7-user version.
red_flags: Identical brand color palette used by suspect
Keyword stuffing of brand name in description
Extremely low user count compared to anchor

malicious_clones.name: claude.ai Dark Mode - Dark eye protection theme

The use of identical trademarked artwork without authorization, paired with the low user count (65 vs 200,000), classifies this as a malicious clone designed to capitalize on the official brand's visual recognition.
red_flags: Use of brand name in title
Visual identity theft for a utility tool

malicious_clones.name: Open Claude AI in New Tab

red_flags: Unknown developer using high-value brand trademark

malicious_clones.name: Claude Metrics

Combined with a very low user count (8) and an unknown developer, this represents a high risk of brand impersonation for the purpose of capturing user data or analytics from the Claude.ai platform.
